# Operator-local workspace files (not project artifacts) — listed explicitly
# so a broad `git add -A` can't sweep them into an unrelated commit (this
# nearly happened on the #1030 branch, 2026-06-07; caught pre-PR).
MASTER_ACTIVATION_GUIDE.md
scripts/_friday_eod_check_one_off.py
start.ps1

audit/cron.log

# nightly-audit runner (audit/runner/nightly_runner.py) runtime artifacts —
# operational, per-run, machine-local; never committed. Reports and
# ALERT-*-runner.md failure artifacts are NOT ignored (they are the findings
# the morning ritual sweeps).
audit/runner-markers.log
audit/transcripts/
audit/manifests/
audit/snapshots/
audit/.nightly-runner.lock
audit/preflight-manifest.json
audit/broker-snapshot.json
audit/reports/selftest-*.md

# Operator-local secret-at-rest files (DSN / connection-string / URL secrets) —
# never committed. Added 2026-07-20 (chore/url-txt-ignore-guard): an untracked
# `url.txt` (DSN-shaped secret) sat at the repo root matched by NO ignore rule,
# one `git add` from being committed. History audit proved it was NEVER tracked.
# Root-anchored so a legitimately-tracked file of the same name in a subdir is
# unaffected; `*.dsn` guards connection-string files anywhere in the tree.
/url.txt
*.dsn
